---
description: Core coding standards for RojgarApp (backend + frontend)
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow these rules for all code in this repository. Full details in `CODING_RULES.md`.

- No function may exceed **30 lines** (excluding signature and blank lines). A function does one thing; split otherwise.
- Max **4 parameters** per function; pass an object/dataclass beyond that.
- **One feature = one package.** Backend: a dedicated Django app. Frontend: a dedicated `features/<name>/` folder. Features must not import each other's internals; share only via `core`/`common`.
- Keep source files under ~200 lines.
- Use descriptive, full-word names. Booleans read as questions (`is_active`).
- No magic strings/numbers; use constants or settings. Secrets come from environment variables only.
- Comment **why**, not **what**. No commented-out code.
- Never silently swallow errors. Validate input at the boundary (serializers/forms).
- Backend flow: `model → serializer → view → url`. Non-trivial logic goes in `services.py`, not the view.
- Each feature package ships with at least basic tests.
